  "_note": "Per-entry _verification_status records sourcing. cross_references.* populated at X.D.1 back-fill (currently all null). The 13-35 00 00 umbrella entry is excluded from entries[] as the parent_category header. The secondary mirror exposes three level-2 sub-trees under 13-35: Judicial Spaces (13-35 11), Legislative Spaces (13-35 13), and Military Spaces (13-35 15). No further sub-trees (e.g. detention/correctional, embassy, civic) appear in the mirror — the mirror coverage of 13-35 terminates at 13-35 15 13. The 20 entries include: one level-3 sub-tree root per sub-group (13-35 11 00, 13-35 13 00, 13-35 15 00), one level-4 courtroom sub-group header (13-35 11 11), seven level-5 courtroom entries (13-35 11 11 11 through 13-35 11 11 21), three judicial-chambers entries (13-35 11 13 through 13-35 11 13 13), two hearing/robing entries (13-35 11 15, 13-35 11 19, 13-35 11 19 11), two legislative entries (13-35 13 11, 13-35 13 13), and two military entries (13-35 15 11, 13-35 15 13). Target of 14 is exceeded because the mirror coverage is dense in the judicial sub-tree. ifc_space_type=INTERNAL applied to all entries as all government spaces in this sub-tree are enclosed interior spaces per IfcSpaceTypeEnum (ISO 16739). Future Sprint Y back-fill from the canonical OCCS PDF (CSI license) may add detention/correctional, embassy, and civic sub-trees and will raise _verification_status from mirror_sourced to occs_verified.",
